    "156146530": {
      "title": "Optimal ordering strategies for seasonal products based on spectrum risk measure and option contract",
      "abstract": "Traditional ordering decisions for seasonal products often focus on minimizing expected cost or maximizing expected profits,which assume decision makers to be risk neutral.In this paper,we incorporate retailer's different risk attitudes by means of spectrum risk measure into the ordering decision model for seasonal products,and discuss the optimal ordering decisions of the retailer under the option contract mechanism.We show that the optimal ordering quantities of cash commodity and option commodity are existent and unique,and then analyze the specific ordering strategy of the retailer who has different risk preferences through the mean-CVaR risk spectrum function.The effects of the retailer's risk attitude,and the price parameters of option contract on the optimal ordering decisions are also analyzed.Finally,we illustrate our theoretical results by some numerical examples."
    }
